# Git Workflow

## Safety

- Always run `git status --short --branch` before pull, commit, or push.
- Do not run destructive git commands (`reset --hard`, force push, checkout over files) unless André explicitly approves.
- Do not commit secrets, `.env` files, credentials, private keys, or production data exports.
- Commit only when the user explicitly asks or when project/session rules require it and no higher-priority instruction forbids it.

## Standard Flow

Local edit -> commit -> push `main` -> André pulls in Codespaces -> test in Codespaces.

When asked to commit/push:
1. Review status, diff, and recent log.
2. Stage only relevant files.
3. Use a clear commit message.
4. Push `origin main` unless the user says not to.
5. Verify status afterward.

## Codespaces Test Commands

After pushing, give André the exact relevant sequence:

```bash
git pull origin main
cd mymoolah-wallet-frontend && npm run build && cd ..   # if wallet frontend changed
cd portal/admin/frontend && npm run build && cd ../../.. # if admin portal changed
./scripts/one-click-restart-and-start.sh                 # main API/wallet only
```

For Admin Portal/disbursement UI testing use:

```bash
./scripts/start-all-services.sh [uat|staging]
```

Never suggest `pm2 restart`, `node server.js`, `npm start`, or any backend restart that bypasses the approved scripts.
